en_743252_0	Lecturers at the Army Directorate of Preventive Medicine and Mental Health at the Colombo Army Hospital, together with several civil counsellors delivered lectures on ‘Suicide Prevention and Problem-Solving Psychological Programme’ on Wednesday (2) at Headquarters 2 (Volunteer) Sri Lanka Light Infantry (SLLI) auditorium in Kelanimulla, under the 14 Division of the Security Force Headquarters - West (SFHQ-West).
en_743252_1	5 Officers and 107 Other Rankers from different establishments in the 14 Division attended the lectures.
en_743252_2	The ongoing educating programme of the Army Directorate of Preventive Medicine and Mental Health has so far conducted several such lectures covering many hundreds of soldiers serving in separate formations.
